==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gadolinium
<hw>Gad`o*lin"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Gadolinite</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare earth
metallic element of the Lanthanide series, with a characteristic
spectrum, found associated with yttrium and other rare earth elements.
Symbol, <it>Gd</it>; it has an atomic number of 64, an atomic weight of
157.25 (C=12.011), and a valence of +3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

